[SN]TITLE[SN]
African elephants may be shortest-sleeping mammals

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
African elephants already hold the title for largest land animal, but now they might be about to break another record... for least sleep.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
2 March 2017 Last updated at 06:38 GMT
Researchers have found that African elephants in the wild sleep an average of two hours a day and regularly go nearly two days without sleep.
They monitored two African female elephants in Chobe National Park, Botswana, for 35 days.
